{
  "texts": [
    "While ergodicity in turbulent flows is not guaranteed in general, it can reasonably be assumed for this setup [1].",
    "Direct numerical simulation of the NSE for this test case is computationally infeasible due to the wide range of scales in turbulence.",
    "Consequently, Large-Eddy Simulation (LES) is employed using the commercial solver ANSYS Fluent [112].",
    "LES resolves the large, energy-containing eddies explicitly, while the effects of smaller subgrid-scale motions are modeled [113,114].",
    "This is achieved through spatial filtering, which decomposes a flow variable φ t (x) into a filtered (resolved) component φ t (x) and a subgrid-scale component φt (x),φ t (x) = φ t (x) + φt (x),(23)with the filter defined implicitly by the computational grid."
  ]
}